Dodge Caliber A real performance bargain
The 2009 Dodge Caliber is classed as a compact car five door, five passengers. Isn’t easily identifiable, it includes hatchback, wagon and minivan design elements. There are four different four-cylinder engines, with manual transmission or with a continuously-variable automatic. It is affordable and fuel efficient with an EPA evaluated 24/30 city/highway mpg in its most frugal form. At the other end of the scale is the SRT4 version has a turbocharged engine generating 285 horsepower. With a slightly higher starting price, it is a performance bargain!
The front seats are comfortable, with plenty of headroom, and there is plenty of cargo space. The interior is functional with a folding rear seats that has the tilt adjustment and the optional front passenger seat folds flat. Thus, you can carry long materials. The 2009 Dodge Caliber offers several innovative options, especially for a car of this price category, including an air conditioned compartment in the glove box to chill water bottles, and a stereo attached to the tailgate converts the rear in small sound stage for beach parties or the famous football tailgates for example.
For 2009, some minor changes were made. There are four new body colors, anti-lock brakes standard on the SXT, sound insulation improvements and a 1.8-liter engine that consumes much less, or 30mpg on the highway. By cons, all-wheel drive was available for the R / T is no longer available. Read the full article... http://www.autospb.ca/en-CA/blog/test-drive/dodge-caliber-a-real-performance-bargain.aspx﻿
